cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes an integration of ADMM with the method of stochastic variance reduced gradient (SVRG) for optimization in machine learning. It may also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it discusses optimization solvers and their convergence rates. Additionally, it may belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with control and optimization problems. Finally, it may belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as optimization is a fundamental component of many computer vision algorithms.
